From 78a9c9ee601dfe5b8afb5d2a15d20492b9acf653 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 15:19:50 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] net: ethernet: tc956x: Fix API changes for kernel 6.18
 compatibility

Update the driver to compile cleanly against kernel 6.18 by addressing
the following deprecated or changed APIs:

strlcpy() removal (kernel 6.8):
  Replace all strlcpy() calls with strscpy().

ethtool EEE struct rename (kernel 6.9):
  Replace struct ethtool_eee with struct ethtool_keee.Update EEE
  capability reporting to use linkmode_copy() directly on the
  ethtool_keee bitmaps. Replace phydev->eee_broken_modes with
  phydev->eee_disabled_modes.

phylink validate -> mac_get_caps (kernel 6.7):
  Replace the phylink_mac_ops.validate callback with mac_get_caps().

phy_loopback() signature change:
  Add the new speed argument to all phy_loopback() call sites.

phy_lookup_setting() -> phy_caps_lookup():
  Replace the removed tc956x_phy_check_valid() helper and its
  phy_lookup_setting() dependency with the new phy_caps_lookup() API.

hrtimer_setup() (kernel 6.15):
  Replace the two-step hrtimer_init() + function pointer assignment
  with the combined hrtimer_setup() call.

Upstream-Status: Submitted [https://github.com/TC956X/TC9564_Host_Driver/pull/4]
Signed-off-by: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
